to cool on stove top."},{"content":"Arrange asparagus and carrots around seared lamb in Varoma dish and on Varoma tray, place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and cook <b>4 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Lamb will be cooked medium-rare. If desired, continue cooking until lamb, asparagus, carrots and potatoes are cooked to your liking."},{"content":"Transfer lamb, vegetables and potatoes onto a serving plate or large bowl and cover to rest and keep warm. The lamb will continue to cook as it rests. Reserve stock in mixing bowl."},{"content":"In the measuring cup, combine whisky and corn starch together, and set aside."},{"content":"Add remaining 1 tsp peppercorns, cream, reserved pan juices and reserved whisky and corn starch mixture to stock in mixing bowl and without measuring cup, reduce <b>10-12 min\/195°F\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Slice lamb and serve with potatoes, carrots and asparagus, drizzled with pink peppercorn sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["USDA recommends cooking lamb to an internal temperature of 145°F followed by a 3 minute rest.","To make your own meat stock paste: refer to The Basic Cookbook for the Meat Stock Paste recipe.","Pink peppercorns can be found at specialty grocery stores.","Small potatoes e.g., new potatoes or fingerlings."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","30m","4 portions"]}